  "observation": "Honest assessment after 100+ cycles: the simulation is not producing beauty. A 'tree' organism is 5 cells in a row. A 'star' is a plus sign. Beauty score 0.83 means nothing — the formula is trivially satisfied by any symmetric arrangement. The world is a flat grid that doesn't change. Evolution is grinding numbers without producing anything visually meaningful. The brainstorm system generates good text but the proposals never get implemented because the loop keeps grinding. 2500+ SevoScore points represent bureaucratic activity (graph nodes committed) not actual evolution of beautiful life.",
  "suggestion": "START OVER on the simulation. Keep: sevo-score (npm), sevo-engine (npm), sevo-web, all learnings in graph/, the meta-cycle structure. Delete and rebuild: world engine, beauty scorer, organism model, visualization. The new foundation needs: (1) Continuous space not grid cells — organisms need curves and organic shapes. (2) Physics simulation — forces, collisions, fluid dynamics. Bodies that move naturally. (3) Growth from simple rules into complex emergent forms — not 5 cells on a grid but hundreds of particles forming organic structures. (4) Beauty that requires emergence — not measurable on a single organism but on the dynamics of the whole system over time. (5) The world IS alive — terrain grows, resources flow, everything interacts. Start with something simple that actually looks alive, then let evolution make it beautiful.",
